    • Method Detail

      • after

        boolean after(DateTime dateTime,
              DateTime earliestDateTime)
        Validates that the supplied date-time is after the supplied earliest date-time.

        Note that passing a null value to any of the parameters causes validation to fail.

        Parameters:
        dateTime - The date-time to check.
        earliestDateTime - The earliest valid date-time.
        Returns:
        True if the validation is successful, false if it is unsuccessful.

        Returns:

      • betweenExclusive

        boolean betweenExclusive(DateTime dateTime,
                         DateTime earliestDateTime,
                         DateTime latestDateTime)
        Validates that the supplied date-time is between the supplied earliest and latest date-times (excluding the interval date-times themselves).

        Note that passing a null value to any of the parameters causes validation to fail.

        Parameters:
        dateTime - The date-time to check.
        earliestDateTime - The earliest valid date-time.
        latestDateTime - The latest valid date-time.
        Returns:
        True if the validation is successful, false if it is unsuccessful.
